1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
SmartOffice AI - Complete OAuth Demo for Google Verification

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
This demo shows Gmail and Calendar integration with read-only OAuth scopes

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Opening SmartOffice AI at www.smartoffice-ai.com

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Logging in with test account: mogabli12@gmail.com

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Dashboard successfully loaded - showing navigation menu

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Dashboard displays: Email, Calendar, and Reports features

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Now we'll demonstrate Gmail OAuth integration

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Clicking "Connect Gmail" button to start OAuth flow

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Google OAuth consent screen appears

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Consent screen shows: "SmartOffice AI wants to access your Google Account"

11
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:58,000
App is requesting: "See and download your email messages and settings"

12
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:04,000
This is the gmail.readonly scope - READ-ONLY access only

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Important: Notice there is a blue link to show detailed permissions

14
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Clicking "See the 1 service SmartOffice AI wants to access"

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Link expands to show full permission details

16
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Gmail.readonly scope permissions displayed

17
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Shows: "View your email messages and settings" (read-only)

18
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Key point: The app ONLY reads emails - never sends, deletes, or modifies

19
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Read-only access means your inbox stays completely safe and unchanged

20
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:53,000
The app uses this to categorize emails by priority (Urgent/Important/Normal)

21
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:59,000
No emails can be deleted, moved, or modified by SmartOffice AI

22
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Now clicking "Continue" to authorize Gmail access

23
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Authorization in progress... redirecting back to app

24
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Gmail authorization successful!

25
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:21,000
App is now loading your Gmail inbox

26
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Inbox successfully loaded - showing last 15 emails

27
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Each email displays: Subject, Sender, Date, and Preview

28
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Emails categorized with AI priority badges (when OpenAI credits available)

29
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Gmail integration complete - all data accessed in read-only mode

30
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Now demonstrating Google Calendar OAuth integration

31
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Clicking "Connect Calendar" button to start Calendar OAuth flow

32
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Google OAuth consent screen appears for Calendar

33
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Consent screen shows Calendar access request

34
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:12,000
App requesting: "See and download any calendar you can access"

35
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:18,000
This is the calendar.readonly scope - READ-ONLY access only

36
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Clicking the blue link to show detailed calendar permissions

37
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Link expands to display full permission details

38
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Calendar.readonly scope allows: See personal and shared calendars

39
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:43,000
✓ See and download calendar events and event details

40
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:49,000
✓ See email addresses of people on calendar events

41
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:55,000
✗ NO permission to create new events

42
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:02,000
✗ NO permission to edit or modify existing events

43
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:08,000
✗ NO permission to delete calendar events

44
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:14,000
This is strictly READ-ONLY access for weekly report generation

45
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Your calendar data remains completely secure and unchanged

46
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:27,000
The app only reads event information to include in automated reports

47
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Now clicking "Continue" to authorize Calendar access

48
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Authorization in progress... redirecting back to app

49
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Calendar authorization successful!

50
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:49,000
App is now loading your Google Calendar events

51
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Calendar events successfully loaded - showing next 20 upcoming events

52
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Each event displays: Title, Date/Time, Location, and Description

53
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Events can be viewed directly in Google Calendar via provided links

54
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Calendar integration complete - all data accessed in read-only mode

55
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Optional: Showing Report Generation feature

56
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Users can generate PDF or Word reports with email and calendar summaries

57
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:29,000
All report data comes from read-only access - no source data modifications

58
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Security Summary: SmartOffice AI uses only read-only OAuth scopes

59
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:42,000
✓ gmail.readonly - View emails only, never send/delete/modify

60
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:48,000
✓ calendar.readonly - View events only, never create/edit/delete

61
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Both scopes ensure complete user data privacy and security

62
00:05:54,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Thank you for reviewing SmartOffice AI's OAuth implementation
